@node inventscorner "Ivent's Corner"
@toc contents
		       @{fg shine}-= Ivent's Corner - Boss Machine =-@{fg text}
		            Written by: @{"Kevin Saunders" link kevinsaunders}

 - = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = = -
                           Hi Everyone,

I have had a lot of various Amiga magazines asking for exclusive content 
for Boss Machine for the Amiga. The difficulty is being fair and giving 
all the new magazines the same opportunity, assets or information and 
insight.  My focus to be honest is to try to make the best game possible 
and any time spent really needs to go into the game. I post a ton of 
behind the scenes on my Patreon and this is the best way to get the latest 
information and every now and then show off a few ideas on our Youtube.  
Dan and I have started some Dev streams for example.

Another shoot em up is coming to the Amiga.  @{i}Boss Machine@{ui} for AGA 
Amigas.

@{b}History:@{ub}
The project started at the end of 2019 with some initial ideas using 
existing art assets I had created for various other shooters (Underthreat, 
Fatal Danger).  The original game started out as an ECS shooter, with Duel 
playfield, 8 colours foreground and 8 background.  

Daniel Stephens and Australian game developer (coder) first contacted me 
back when James Roberts and Myself created a Kickstarter game called 
@{i}Iridium@{ui} for the PC/Switch a few years ago.

Below is a Question/Answer section for Boss Machine (I have written these 
questions but some are what people have been asking recently :)

@{b}Inspiration for the game?@{ub}
One of the bigger inspirations is @{i}Thunder Force IV@{ui} for the Sega 
Megadrive - Technosoft - 1992). However inspiration certainly comes from a 
lot of other games.  Dan is keen on replicating some of the gameplay of 
this style of shooter on the Amiga. 

@{b}Will there be an ECS/OCS version?@{ub}
Sorry no, we both decided early on that AGA was the way to go.  You can 
however see some of the early ECS tech demos on our youtube.  We may 
release the tech demo so people with ECS machines and play it.  For me AGA 
back in the day never really got the opportunity to show off it's 
capabilities.

@{b}When will Boss Machine be released?@{ub}
Dan and I are aiming for the end of 2022, but we can't promise any actual 
dates, we use our spare time to create and discuss ideas.  

@{b}Why does it take so long to produce a game?@{ub}
Various factors.  Family, Work and other Projects. For me I have a few 
projects going at the moment.  Nova is a new game for the PC similar to 
Jetpac on the Spectrum. Reshoot Proxima III and Aquabyss are my two other 
Amiga projects, both also have a 2022 release date.  I do work on other 
assets for the Amiga community and in the next day or so plan to complete 
the promotional work for this years Amiga Art Contest (Sorry Doug will get 
that to you very soon).

@{b}How many levels does the game have?@{ub}
I'm aiming for 6 as the minimum, I'd love to see at least 3 levels similar 
to the Lava level you may have seen on Dan's Youtube. Another 3 levels 
that closer looks like R-Type, no parallax scrolling but we will have 
other effects such as copper changes to the background and hardware 
sprites overlaid on the foreground to give some parallaxing effects in 
some areas.  I have probably about level 12 concepts at various stages of 
completion. These designs are painted using Photoshop and Procreate and
then converted to Amiga indexed palettes.

@{b}How many people in your team?@{ub}
4 people at this time, Daniel Stephens (coder), Kevin Saunders (graphics), 
Martin Ahman (music) and Tony Aksnes (betatester)

@{b}Will the game have any intro or storyline attached?@{ub}
I do aim at adding towards the end of the design of the main game.  To me 
it's possibly far too limiting to have a story pre-written when we are 
enjoying the process of making something new and exciting for Amigans and 
that storyline might actually limit some ideas for the game we want to 
create. However towards the end of the game design phase I plan on 
threading a storyline throughout with various animations, cut scenes.

@{b}The Future, will there be Boss Machine II?@{ub}
Not sure, depending on the success of the game and if Dan and I want to 
create something else :)

@{b}Will there be a @{i}Making of Boss Machine@{ui} Book?@{ub}
Yes!, I am currently creating an eBook of all the behind the scenes to 
creating this game. This is another way of seeing and reading about all 
the details, thoughts and changes throughout the timeline of game 
development.  I plan to also add a page for each of the developers to 
write a little something.

@{b}Why not an actual physical Book@{ub}
The cost and demand for such a book is mainly the issue, I don't believe 
there would be much of a demand and books usually are cheaper to produce 
once you start bigger productions of them.  I am considering creating a 
few physical books for the developers and maybe raffle off one or two 
extras.

@{b}Any other thoughts?@{ub}
With the recent A500mini release I have talked to Dan about possibly a 
WHload/USB version of the game for that machine, I plan on buying one to 
test on.  This will be quite exciting I believe especially if people who 
buy the hardware would like to play new games in 2022.

@{b}Where can I get more info about Boss Machine?@{ub}

Our Facebook Site: 
https://www.facebook.com/bossmachineamiga
Dan's Youtube: 
https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC5HbKXgW6xTp2jFfhmtAs0g/videos
My Patreon: 
https://www.patreon.com/KevinSaunders
EAB Amiga Forum: 
http://eab.abime.net/showthread.php?t=99887&highlight=Boss+machine

Between the three sites I believe it gives you a nice variety of content 
for the moment. I have Twitter, Instagram, Discord and other blogs that I 
post on to also.

Thank you for your time, I hope you found this read interesting :)

A final thankyou to my Patreons: 
(each one will receive a ebook of the Making of the Game)*

Daniel Stephens | Niels Peter Frandsen | Andreas Deubein 
10MinuteAmigaRetroCast | Stale Kopperud | The Amiga Show | Will Green 
Tony Aksnes | Seb V | Richard Lawenstein | Michael Jurisch 
Marcus Schmitt | Predseda | G S | Mahendra T.

@endnode

